description:
During spring and summertime, we observed that the space underneath the canopy is heating up quite to much in direct sunshine. People therefore tend to sit underneath a tree to receive additional shadows.


Our tests with small fans were not successful. They have not enough power to get the temperature down. We had 36°C temperatures when sitting directly in the sun (and 30° when sitting under a tree).


We also observed that opening the canopy just a bit makes a huge difference in terms of cooling, especially when there is a small breeze going on.
